# Phase 62 Wave 0 — caret rendering coverage for CREATE error paths.
#
# Wave 0 stages this fixture as a no-op (the `halt` directive stops
# sqllogictest after the preamble). Plan 04 (Wave 3) populates the actual
# `statement error` blocks once Plans 02–03 restore caret rendering via
# parse_function on FALLBACK_OVERRIDE deferral.
#
# Behavioural properties pinned (from RESEARCH.md §6):
#   B1: caret renders for malformed CREATE (missing '(')
#   B2: caret renders for clause typo (`TBLES` → suggest `TABLES`)
#   B3: caret renders for prefix near-miss (`CRETAE`)

require semantic_views

statement ok
LOAD semantic_views;

halt

# Phase 62 Plan 04 will populate these. Coverage:
#   - missing '(' after TABLES
#   - typo 'TBLES' instead of 'TABLES'
#   - near-miss prefix 'CRETAE SEMANTIC VIEW'
# Each `statement error` block expects substring of validator message AND
# presence of "LINE 1:" + a caret line in the error text.
